g.text: Interfacing: The chain trails off into the ocean, connecting the island to the supply depot on the coast.
Rhetoric: Enemies of madness. Lunacy. Of the apocalypse taking place here.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant looks at the mechanism overhead. "Ah, yes... so it seems."
Interfacing: Enemies of the Commune of Revachol.
Kim Kitsuragi: "From enemies." He looks up ahead. "Enemies of the Commune of Revachol. This seafort was a revolutionary fortification, I believe..."
(Point to it.) "This leads to the depot in Land's End."
Rhetoric: Do not be too eager to greet these enemies, black hearted cavalier -- they were also the enemies of Revachol.
Rhetoric: Of the future. Enemies of mankind.
Cuno: "Dunno, pig, doesn't look like we behind a door right now -- just Cuno's 2 cents of course."
You: This means I *sorta* got into the depot door.
You: "This means I *sorta* got into the depot door."
You: "What do you think it was used for?"
Interfacing: For bringing supplies: munitions and fuel. You could also raise it, in order to lock the Western bay of Revachol.
Kim Kitsuragi: "For bringing munitions to the island, maybe? And supplies. You could also *lock* the bay, when you raise the chain."
Visual Calculus: As a defensive measure locking off that side of the bay.
Cuno: The boy stares at the mechanism. "Cool fucking chain."
Cuno: "Fuck does Cuno know?" He shrugs his shoulders. "Cuno would use it to bring shit to the island."
